            <Text fill="#f08d76" layoutX="20.0" layoutY="31.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Have a listen to I Will Survive by Gloria Gaynor. The sequence is Am (i) - Dm (vi) - G (VII) - Cmaj7 (III) - Fmaj7 (VI) - Bm7b5 (ii) - E (V). If we take just the roots of the chords we have A, D, G, C, F, B, E and back to A. You might notice that the root of each chord is an interval of a fifth lower than the chord which precedes it, hence the name circle of fifths!" wrappingWidth="480.0" AnchorPane.leftAnchor="10.0" AnchorPane.topAnchor="60.0">
